   <h4>How to Prevent Test/Quiz Anxiety</h4>
  Tests and quizes can cause lots of stress, especially if it means the difference of a higher or lower letter grade. With all of these high stakes, you could mess up on the obvious questions or forget all the information you studied seconds before you start.
  <ul>Here's some helpful tips to prevent/decrease test/quiz axiety:
  <br><br>
  <li>If you aren't studying for your tests or quizes, please study everything diligently. Go back to old tests/quizes, study guides, and homework. Most of the anxiety goes away if you come in prepared. NEVER cram the night before, this causes the feeling of being underprepared.</li>
  <li>Just before the test/quiz begins, take deep breaths. Imagine yourself in a calm place. This exercise calms your brain down.</li>
  <li>Get a good night's sleep the night before the test/quiz. It's important to feel energized and remember that all of the information sticks.</li>
   </ul>
  
